# Unused Imports (Always)

When editing any file:

- **Remove every unused import** before considering the edit done.
- Do not leave orphaned imports (e.g. after deleting a type, refactoring, or renaming).
- Prefer fixing imports in the same change that caused them to become unused.

### Examples

**Java**

```java
// ❌ BAD — unused imports left in
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;   // unused
import java.util.Set;   // unused

public class Example {
    public List<String> getItems() { ... }
}
```

```java
// ✅ GOOD — only used imports
import java.util.List;

public class Example {
    public List<String> getItems() { ... }
}
```

**TypeScript / JavaScript**

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — unused imports
import { foo, bar, baz } from './module';  // baz unused

// ✅ GOOD — only what is used
import { foo, bar } from './module';
```

If you add or change code, run through the imports and delete any that are no longer referenced.
